article.description: Ben Millaud-Meunier scored a career-high 32 points with six 3-pointers as St. Francis (Pa.) cruised past Division II Westminster 103-72 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: St. Francis flashes past D-II Westminster 103-72
article.linkText: St. Francis flashes past D-II Westminster 103-72
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Ben Millaud-Meunier scored a career-high 32 points with six 3-pointers as St. Francis (Pa.) cruised past Division II Westminster 103-72 on Tuesday night. The Red Flash (1-1) jumped out to a 25-7 lead just seven-and-a-half minutes into the game. Millaud-Meunier missed two of his first three shots -- all 3-pointers -- but finished with 8-of-15 shooting, including 6 of 12 from distance. Malik Harmon added 19 points with nine assists, Basil Thompson 15 points and Isaiah Blackmon 14 points on 7-of-10 shooting. The Titans (0-2) rallied after falling behind so quickly, launching a 30-14 run to pull to 39-37 on a 3-pointer by Jarret Vrabel with 4:37 left in the first half. Vrabel finished with 11 points, Paul Carswell led with 14. St. Francis outrebounded the Titans 53-32 and had 18 assists on 34 field goals.
